This movie is a true masterpiece. I used to hate animated movies. I thought they were bland, inane, and generally a poorly constructed medium. One day I was bored. All of my hobbies felt old, and I needed something to do with my life. I looked saw a promotion for this movie by the acclaimed reviewer and critic "Jacksfilms" He described at as a sort of magic, something truly anyone young or old will love. So I watched this movie, and it it helped me understand this medium. I now have decided to live out my life as a hermit on a remote island on Alaska. This is my last action on the internet, and I now more confident than ever of this. Thank you T.J. Miller.
